lastor_ver02/data/sn78003992/00340580928/1945083101/0294.pdf", "segment_count": 12, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn78003992/1945-08-31/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_alastor_ver02/data/sn78003992/00340580928/1945083101/0294.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn78003992/1945-08-31/ed-1/?sp=1"], "batch": ["ohi_alastor_ver02"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/ohio/", "2/united states/ohio/summit/", "3/united states/ohio/summit/akron/"], "contributor": ["ohio history connection, columbus, oh"], "date": "1945-08-31", "dates": ["1945-08-31"], "description": ["So Labor May Know OPEN LETTER TO SENATORS TAFT AND BURTON AND SOME OHIO CONGRESSMEN Gentlemen We the people of Ohio are some what amazed by your antics in the past few months We are suddenly made aware 1 of your abysmal ig norance or 2 otkr clear foresight It stuns us to think that we the people saw all this coming and you did not We speak of course of our plan less reconversion period While we were shouting in our Union halls and our little gatherings about the im pending catastrophe you dismissed our fears with a light nothing to it at all While we urged actiona plan for Peaceyou favored inaction We the people are particularly dis turbed by the way you treated the National Planning Resources Board You knocked that one out four years ago saying at the time that planning for the peace was visionary and unrealistic Overriding protests of the late President Roosevelt you re fused to continue the Board Now we ask who was rightyou or Roose velt Are you prepared to take re sponsibility for killing the Planning and Resources Board yt the people also woyld like you to explain your recent"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-03-24T16:08:15.715Z", "group": ["ndnp/ohi", "ohio-historical-society-awardee"], "hass